abstract: Some West Virginians have a message for Sen. Joe Manchin regarding his vote to impeach the president: Thanks.
snippet: Some West Virginians have a message for Sen. Joe Manchin regarding his vote to impeach the president: Thanks.
lead_paragraph: HUNTINGTON, W.Va. — Some West Virginians have a message for Sen. Joe Manchin regarding his vote to impeach the president: Thanks.
headline_main: After Impeachment, Manchin Comes Home to Warm Welcome in WV
headline_print_headline: After Impeachment, Manchin Comes Home to Warm Welcome in WV

abstract: First Iowa, then New Hampshire. Now the president is on a Western trip, and basing it in Las Vegas, days before the Nevada caucuses.
snippet: First Iowa, then New Hampshire. Now the president is on a Western trip, and basing it in Las Vegas, days before the Nevada caucuses.
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — President Trump is not exactly a fan of life on the road.

lead_paragraph: Though the coronavirus continues to spread in China, its growth appears to be slowing: On Wednesday, for the second straight day, the authorities reported fewer than 2,000 new cases. Still, public health officials have warned against excessive optimism. Here are the latest updates from around the world and maps of where the virus has spread.

lead_paragraph: CHICAGO — When Patti Blagojevich made repeated public pleas for her husband's release from federal prison, there was no mistaking her intended audience: President Donald Trump.

abstract: President Donald Trump trolled his political enemies Wednesday in the first of three rallies in three days in the West as Democrats vied in neighboring Nevada to be the one to challenge him in the November election.

abstract: The Washington publication The Hill issued a lengthy report on Wednesday finding fault with several articles by journalist John Solomon that it published last year and were used as discredited narratives by President Donald Trump and many of his supporters in their fight against impeachment.

abstract: The Trump administration completed the fewest cleanups of toxic Superfund sites last year than any administration since the program’s first years in the 1980s, figures released by the Environmental Protection Agency indicated Wednesday.
snippet: The Trump administration completed the fewest cleanups of toxic Superfund sites last year than any administration since the program’s first years in the 1980s, figures released by the Environmental Protection Agency indicated Wednesday.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration completed the fewest cleanups of toxic Superfund sites last year than any administration since the program’s first years in the 1980s, figures released by the Environmental Protection Agency indicated Wednesday.
headline_main: Toxic Superfund Cleanups Decline to More Than 30-Year Low
headline_print_headline: Toxic Superfund Cleanups Decline to More Than 30-Year Low

abstract: Mr. Blagojevich, the former Democratic governor of Illinois, spoke of having his sentence for corruption commuted by President Trump and described himself as a “freed political prisoner.”
snippet: Mr. Blagojevich, the former Democratic governor of Illinois, spoke of having his sentence for corruption commuted by President Trump and described himself as a “freed political prisoner.”
lead_paragraph: CHICAGO — Rod R. Blagojevich emerged from his brick bungalow into shivering cold air on Wednesday, coatless, tieless and remorseless. Mr. Blagojevich, the former governor of Illinois, who had been in a Colorado prison until a day earlier, denounced a broken justice system, thanked President Trump for commuting his sentence and insisted that he had done nothing illegal.

abstract: A Florida woman who got clemency from President Donald Trump while serving prison time for a $205 million Medicare fraud scam said Wednesday her case was brought to Trump's attention by a woman who herself got clemency at the urging of reality TV star Kim Kardashian West.
snippet: A Florida woman who got clemency from President Donald Trump while serving prison time for a $205 million Medicare fraud scam said Wednesday her case was brought to Trump's attention by a woman who herself got clemency at the urging of reality TV ...
lead_paragraph: HIALEAH, Fla. — A Florida woman who got clemency from President Donald Trump while serving prison time for a $205 million Medicare fraud scam said Wednesday her case was brought to Trump's attention by a woman who herself got clemency at the urging of reality TV star Kim Kardashian West.
headline_main: Trump Clemency Recipient Links Her Case to Kardashian West
